{"lemma":"مُفْرِطٌ","slug":"مُفْرِطٌ","root":"ف.ر.ط","root_slug":"ف-ر-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ط","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُفْرِطٌ","root":"فرط","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33605"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"excessive"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of أَفْرَطَ (ʔafraṭa)","tags":["form-of","participle","passive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb أَفْرَطَ (ʔafraṭa)."},"ipa":["/muf.ritˤ/","/muf.ratˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33605","headword_ar":"مُفْرِطٌ","root":"frT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Exceeding the due bounds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"just limits; acting extravagantly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excessive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to anything; as, for instance, tallness, and shortness. (TA.) It is said in a trad. of 'Alee, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taraY AljaAhila A_al~aA muforiTFA A^awo mufar~iTFA","text_ar":"لَا تَرَى الجَاهِلَ اـَلَّا مُفْرِطًا اَوْ مُفَرِّطًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou wilt not see the ignorant otherwise than exceeding the due bounds in what he doth or falling short of what he ought therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforaTN","text_ar":"مُفْرَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}